text: Hyponephele is a genus of butterflies of the subfamily Satyrinae in the family Nymphalidae. Most range from Europe into central Asia with a few in northern Africa. They are commonly called meadowbrowns. ==Species== Listed alphabetically:"Hyponephele Muschamp, 1915" at Markku Savela's Lepidoptera and Some Other Life Forms *Hyponephele amardaea (Lederer, 1869)
